metadata.name: Geometric colorful shapes 3 #25
metadata.description:
This art tool uses an algorithmic approach that includes genetic and selection processes to generate unique and colorful abstract shapes. With the ability to adjust various parameters, each design is truly one-of-a-kind, and you can easily save and share your creations using our unique hash function. So go ahead, get creative, and let the program surprise you with its endless possibilities! Remember, the program is the only creator of these colorful shapes, thanks to its algorithmic approach, and if you like the result, you can support my previous projects.
The program has a default resolution of 1500x1500.

metadata.name: Zug #101
metadata.description:
Zug is the German word for train, but it also translates to 'a force that pulls in a specific direction' which feels very fitting, though it might remain unclear in which direction exactly.

The image is build layering around 9000 transparent strokes grouped so that the resemblance of a passing train is created. Most strokes are blurred, some are repeating.

All editions share the same base color palette. From it three different palettes are derived for the light, medium and dark colors. Press 'c' to get a better idea of how this works.

Initial sketch made for the Weekly Creative Coding Challenge hosted by Raphaël de Courville (@Sableraph).

Commands:
f = fullscreen toggle
b = change window background color
c = color palettes overlay toggle
s = save image at 1080 x 1920 pixels
p = save image at 3240 x 5760 pixels

metadata.name: Helix #39
metadata.description:
"Helix" is a 100% code generative real time 3D sculpture. An interactive study to lighting and color. Move your mouse to set the light's position. Press the "V" key to view the object from different angles (rotation)

CONTROLS

KEYS:
- V: Render a different view (object view angle) on each key press
- B: Toggle Backlight (on/off)
- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset/reload
- SPACEBAR: Toggle light's position auto-update and also toggle (enable/disable) mouse move interactivity

MOUSE:
- Move: Moves (set) the light's position
- Click: Toggle light's position auto-update and mouse move interactivity (the same as the SPACEBAR)

----
Made with p5js (use WebGL canvas)

© May 2023  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Travelling Gondola #4
metadata.description:
The Traveler says:

-Each planet has a story, in this gondola you can talk to the stars, confess to the moon... I've seen the beginning and end of ages, slowly... slowly I travel and witness the passage of everything, I'm in no hurry if time is slower than me, and one day we will reach the singularity.

Is it the end?

-

Interactivity:

[ARROW UP] - Ticket Up.
[ARROW DOWN] - Ticket Down.
[MOUSE HOVER ON TICKET] - Shows what each feature defines.

[A] - Render a 20 frames gif.
[S] - Render a 40 frames gif.
[D] - Render a 60 frames gif.
 
[Z] - Save a printscreen of canvas.
[X] - Up/Down ballons.
[C] - Open/Close blueprint.

-

Travelling Gondola have 7 Features:
-Gunwale
-Hull Sides
-Hull Middle
-Biome
-Superficie
-Vegetation
-Atmosphere



by Gen Doodler | twitter.com/GenDoodler

metadata.name: Curtains #59
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js
